</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="55">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="22" pageNumber="55" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="toviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="55">Cyrtandra toviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique within Marquesan 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="22" pageNumber="55" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="55">Cyrtandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its peltate leaves and small campanulate calyx. In fact, it could well represent a separate introduction of the genus to the Marquesas Islands.
</paragraph>
